            <para>Refer to the appropriate chassis manual for cable adjustment.</para>
            <para>The DT/DTI-466 A and B Series Engines utilize either a Bowden Wire Shut-Off (BWSO) or an Electric
                Shut-Off (ESO).
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Bowden Wire Shut-Off (BWSO) (Manual Shut-Off)</emph>
            </para>
            <para>Two variations of the Bowden Wire Shut-Off are used as shown in
                <emph type="bold">Figures
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4500507">5.7</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ,
                <emph type="bold">
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4500508">5.8</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ,
                <emph type="bold">
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4500509">5.9</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                and
                <emph type="bold">
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4500510">5.10</hotlnk>.
                </emph>
                Each variation has been modified to improve the BWSO assembly's resistance to corrosion. Refer to
                CGES-200-2, Section 6 for detailed information about the BWSO modifications.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>VERIFY THAT THE BWSO IS ADJUSTED TO ALLOW FULL RUN BY VISUALLY INSPECTING THE ASSEMBLY. THE
                        BOWDEN WIRE ROD MUST BE FULLY SEATED IN THE ROD GUIDE SCREW WHEN IN THE FULL RUN POSITION. IF
                        NOT FULLY SEATED, REFER TO THE CHASSIS MANUAL FOR CABLE ADJUSTMENT OR RECONDITION THE BWSO AS
                        FOLLOWS:
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
